  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient with Obesity hypoventilation Syndrome (BMI≥ 30 kg/m2 and diurnal PaCO2 ≥
             45mmHg at diagnosis after exclusion of others causes of hypoventilation)

          -  18 to 75 years old

          -  In stable state but treated by nocturnal NIPPV for more than 3 months and adherent to
             NIPPV (above 4h/night).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patient treated with additional long term Oxygen therapy

          -  Patient previously treated by AVAPS mode or IVAPS mode
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
